WEBVTT

00:01:28.247 --> 00:01:32.845
because it's not up to us
whether what we do is any good,

00:01:32.869 --> 00:01:34.931
and if history has taught us anything,

00:01:34.955 --> 00:01:37.702
the world is an extremely
unreliable critic.

00:01:38.178 --> 00:01:39.333
Right?

00:01:39.730 --> 00:01:41.177
So you have to ask yourself:

00:01:41.891 --> 00:01:45.544
Do you think human creativity matters?

00:01:46.649 --> 00:01:48.644
Well, hmm.

00:01:48.668 --> 00:01:52.966
Most people don't spend a lot of time
thinking about poetry. Right?

00:01:52.990 --> 00:01:54.215
They have a life to live,

00:01:54.239 --> 00:01:57.349
and they're not really that concerned
with Allen Ginsberg's poems

00:01:57.373 --> 00:01:58.699
or anybody's poems,

00:01:58.723 --> 00:02:01.270
until their father dies,